# Dashboard Layout Consistency (Mandatory)

All pages inside the `(couple)`, `(vendor)`, and `(admin)` route groups render inside `DashboardShell`, which provides consistent padding via `<main className="flex-1 p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8">`.

## Rules

- **Do NOT** add `max-w-*` with `mx-auto` on the outermost wrapper of a page component. This creates inconsistent distances between the sidebar and the content across pages.
- Page content must fill the available width naturally. The shell's padding is the only spacing between sidebar and content.
- If a specific section within a page needs constrained width (e.g., a form, a modal, a text block), apply `max-w-*` on that inner element only — not on the page's root div.

## Correct

```tsx
export default function SomeDashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-6">
      <h1>Page Title</h1>
      {/* Full-width content */}
      <div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4">...</div>
      {/* Constrained inner section is fine */}
      <form className="max-w-lg">...</form>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Incorrect

```tsx
export default function SomeDashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div className="max-w-5xl mx-auto space-y-6">
      {/* This centers the entire page and creates uneven sidebar gaps */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Scope

This rule applies only to pages rendered inside `DashboardShell`. The public marketing homepage (`app/page.tsx`) and auth pages (`app/(auth)/*`) have their own layouts and are exempt.
